William Hartnell launches the longest running sci-fi series of all time.
Missing episodes are included as reconstructions from recorded audio tracks and surviving production stills, and as animated reconstructions in some cases.

These copies are drawn from the highest quality sources possible, but they are encoded with lower bitrates at 360p resolution to make them ideal for the small screen - phones, tablets, laptops, and monitors.
